properties.headline: Winter Storm Watch issued January 9 at 9:51PM CST until January 12 at 6:00AM CST by NWS Milwaukee/Sullivan WI
properties.description:
...POTENTIAL WINTER STORM THIS WEEKEND...

* WHAT...Ice accumulations between a glaze and a quarter of an
inch and snow accumulations between 1 to 3 inches are possible
Friday evening through Saturday morning. Moderate to heavy
snowfall is likely Saturday afternoon through Saturday night,
with blowing and drifting possible as northeast winds gust to 45
mph. Total snow accumulations of 5 to 12 inches are possible
through Sunday morning.

* WHERE...Portions of south central and southeast Wisconsin.
Generally along and southeast of a line from Janesville to
Milwaukee.

* WHEN...The Winter Storm Watch is from Friday evening through
Sunday Morning.

* IMPACTS...A Winter Storm Watch means there is a potential for
significant snow...sleet...or ice accumulations that may
impact travel. Continue to monitor the latest forecasts.
properties.instruction: Monitor the latest forecasts for updates on this situation.

NWSheadline: WINTER STORM WATCH REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM FRIDAY EVENING THROUGH EARLY SUNDAY MORNING
